{"id":836,"date":"2015-12-15T11:29:03","date_gmt":"2015-12-15T16:29:03","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/?p=836"},"modified":"2017-05-23T12:36:47","modified_gmt":"2017-05-23T16:36:47","slug":"five-part-series-of-articles-on-pollinators-from-penn-state-extension","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/five-part-series-of-articles-on-pollinators-from-penn-state-extension\/","title":{"rendered":"Five New Articles on Pollinators from Penn State Extension"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"fcbkbttn_buttons_block\" id=\"fcbkbttn_left\"><\/div><div class=\"mceTemp\">Members of\u00a0<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http:\/\/ento.psu.edu\/pollinators\" target=\"_blank\">Penn State\u2019s Center for Pollinator Research<\/a>, including Project ICP researcher Dr. Shelby Fleischer,\u00a0and the\u00a0<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http:\/\/extension.psu.edu\/plants\/vegetable-fruit\" target=\"_blank\">Penn State Extension Vegetable and Small Fruit Team<\/a>\u00a0have collaborated to produce\u00a0a five part series of Extension articles describing pollinators, pollinator threats and on-farm conservation strategies, including two articles on pesticide stewardship for pollinators. The series was published between February-October 2015.<\/div>\n<p>To learn\u00a0more, check out the articles here:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http:\/\/extension.psu.edu\/plants\/vegetable-fruit\/news\/2015\/who-are-our-pollinators\" target=\"_blank\">Who Are Our Pollinators?<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http:\/\/extension.psu.edu\/plants\/vegetable-fruit\/news\/2015\/what-can-we-do-to-encourage-native-bees\" target=\"_blank\">What Can We Do To Encourage Native Bees<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http:\/\/extension.psu.edu\/plants\/vegetable-fruit\/news\/2015\/pollinator-declines\" target=\"_blank\">Pollinator Declines<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http:\/\/extension.psu.edu\/plants\/vegetable-fruit\/news\/2015\/pesticides-and-pollinators\" target=\"_blank\">Pesticides and Pollinators<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"http:\/\/extension.psu.edu\/plants\/vegetable-fruit\/news\/2015\/protect-bees-from-pesticides\" target=\"_blank\">Protect Bees from Pesticides<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/five-part-series-of-articles-on-pollinators-from-penn-state-extension\/studentfarm_peponapis_jun10_45\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-837\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-837 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/StudentFarm_Peponapis_Jun10_45-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"StudentFarm_Peponapis_Jun10_45\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/StudentFarm_Peponapis_Jun10_45-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/StudentFarm_Peponapis_Jun10_45-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/StudentFarm_Peponapis_Jun10_45-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><\/a>Squash bees (<em>Peponapis pruinosa<\/em>). Photo: Katharina Ullmann.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Members of\u00a0Penn State\u2019s Center for Pollinator Research, including Project ICP researcher Dr. Shelby Fleischer,\u00a0and the\u00a0Penn State Extension Vegetable and Small Fruit Team\u00a0have collaborated to produce\u00a0a five part series of Extension articles describing pollinators, pollinator threats and on-farm conservation strategies, including&hellip; <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":837,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_exactmetrics_skip_tracking":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_active":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_note":"","_exactmetrics_sitenote_category":0,"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":true